 + filename + \"\\\"\");\n47:            String filename = \"documents-export-\" + today + \".zip\";\n50:            response.setHeader(\"Content-Dispositio‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_011vfeTCn4r3qsN6Q7isjKXU\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:09.789Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_42839c379927":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_42839c379927","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: when streamDocumentZip throws ExportValidationException after the ZipOutputStream closes,\\n# the response is already fully committed (ZIP streaming has started and headers were already sent).\\n# The GlobalExceptionHandler would try to send a 400 response but can't because the response is committed.\\n# Let's check whether streamDocumentZip can throw AFTER partial write starts‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: when streamDocumentZip throws ExportValidationException after the ZipOutputStream closes,\\n# the ‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:18.294Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_8c05c45ca1e5":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_8c05c45ca1e5","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01SrDNswBzxfE6iJFUNF5k1k\"} | Streaming concern analysis: ExportValidationException thrown AFTER ZipOutputStream.close() at line 133\nAt this point response headers were already committed, GlobalExceptionHandler can't return 400\nClient receives a valid HTTP 200 with empty/malformed ZIP body + then exception logged","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01SrDNswBzxfE6iJFUNF5k1k\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:18.332Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_94ce17abd2af":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_94ce17abd2af","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Let's double-check: can validateRequest catch the \\\"no documents\\\" case BEFORE streaming?\\n# validateRequest only checks: clientIds null/empty, size > 200, neither metadata nor documents selected\\n# It does NOT check whether any documents exist. The \\\"no documents\\\" check only happens AFTER streaming.\\n\\n# Also examine: the double-findAllById ‚Äî is there a @Transactional wrapping bot‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Let's double-check: can validateRequest catch the \\\"no documents\\\" case BEFORE streaming?\\n# validateRequ‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:24.520Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_2c9131567903":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_2c9131567903","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01MdCrECroAdqXUXh16L62C8\"} | 66:    public void validateOwnership(Long adminId, List<Long> clientIds) {\n75:    @Transactional(readOnly = true)\n76:    public List<Client> loadOwnedClients(Long adminId, List<Long> clientIds) {\n77:        validateOwnership(adminId, clientIds);\n106:    @Transactional(readOnly = true)\n138:    @Transactional(readOnly = true)\n172:    @Transactional(r‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01MdCrECroAdqXUXh16L62C8\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:26.162Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_f8eaeb778628":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_f8eaeb778628","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: loadOwnedClients is @Transactional, which means both validateOwnership's findAllById \\n# and the second findAllById run in the same transaction ‚Äî this mitigates classic TOCTOU.\\n# However, there's still a logic flaw: validateOwnership checks the clients that EXIST,\\n# but silently ignores IDs that don't exist in the DB. \\n# If clientId 999 (owned by another admin) doesn't ex‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: loadOwnedClients is @Transactional, which means both validateOwnership's findAllById \\n# and the ‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:37.814Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_dea693a137a4":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_dea693a137a4","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_0121ey9JtCLL1DRJEMfpBssu\"} | TOCTOU verdict: Both DB reads are within the same @Transactional(readOnly=true) ‚Äî mitigated.\nNon-existent IDs silently skipped ‚Äî no data leak, but silent ignore without error to caller.","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_0121ey9JtCLL1DRJEMfpBssu\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:37.852Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_b49576d12cbd":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_b49576d12cbd","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Now analyze the ZIP slip / path traversal in detail\\n# Entry path: folderName + \\\"/\\\" + d.getYear() + \\\"/\\\" + d.getFilename()\\n# folderName = sanitizeName(c.getName()) + \\\"-\\\" + c.getId()  [sanitized]\\n# d.getYear() = short ‚Äî numeric, no traversal possible\\n# d.getFilename() = stored in DB from upload\\n\\n# At upload time (DocumentService.upload):\\n# filename = file.getOriginalFilena‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Now analyze the ZIP slip / path traversal in detail\\n# Entry path: folderName + \\\"/\\\" + d.getYear() + \\\"/‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:51.360Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_65881442988d":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_65881442988d","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_017GDtXB3mmkSQRss3ddY2Ns\"} | LocalStorageService.resolve() uses baseDir.resolve(filePath).toAbsolutePath()\nNo check that resolved path is within baseDir ‚Äî path traversal in file READ possible IF filePath in DB is manipulated\nBut filePath is set programmatically at upload time from validated components ‚Äî not user-controlled post-upload","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_017GDtXB3mmkSQRss3ddY2Ns\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:51.380Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_da965930d9bd":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_da965930d9bd","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Summary check: the filename for ZIP entry uses d.getFilename() which comes from DB\\n# At upload: file.getOriginalFilename() is validated then stored. \\n# FileUploadValidator rejects filenames with / \\\\ or ..\\n# So the d.getFilename() in ZIP entry path cannot cause directory traversal.\\n\\n# CONFIRMED: ZIP slip is NOT exploitable through normal upload path because of filename validati‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Summary check: the filename for ZIP entry uses d.getFilename() which comes from DB\\n# At upload: file.get‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:06:58.927Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_cf6b1c4715e0":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_cf6b1c4715e0","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01UkdWCsSRCRNXzpnEqiCwvz\"} | 67:        if (filename == null || filename.isBlank()) {\n97:        if (allowed == null) return;\n98:        String declared = contentType != null ? contentType.split(\";\")[0].trim().toLowerCase(Locale.ROOT) : \"\";\n110:        if (allowed == null) return;","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01UkdWCsSRCRNXzpnEqiCwvz\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:07:00.464Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_3100763f7e1c":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_3100763f7e1c","importance":5,"n