imestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:04.549Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_fe009b74baa6":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_fe009b74baa6","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01RNxLVS9hxHrKcwRvWTbp2K\"} | /Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/contact/service/RateLimiterTest.java:6:class RateLimiterTest {\n/Users/gwang/Develop/accounting-firm/backend/src/test/java/com/gwhaitech/accountingfirm/contact/service/RateLimiterTest.java:10:        RateLimiter limiter = new RateLimiter(5);\n/Users/gwang/Develop/‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01RNxLVS9hxHrKcwRvWTbp2K\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:05.812Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_09ba6cd2fada":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_09ba6cd2fada","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: LocalStorageService.resolve() does NOT check that the resolved path stays within baseDir\\n# This is a defense-in-depth concern, not exploitable through normal flow since filePath is DB-computed\\n# But if DB is compromised, arbitrary file read is possible.\\n\\n# Let's also confirm what the `year` field in ZipEntry path can be:\\n# d.getYear() returns `short` ‚Äî range is -32768 t‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Verify: LocalStorageService.resolve() does NOT check that the resolved path stays within baseDir\\n# This ‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:13.508Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_9ac9b45637d0":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_9ac9b45637d0","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01V1MD87rTGM5YNK2g5Wv3Lc\"} | 31:                                              @RequestParam(\"year\") int year,\n35:        DocumentUploadResult result = documentService.upload(clientId, year, file, uploadedBy);\n42:                                                  @RequestParam(\"year\") int year) {\n43:        return ResponseEntity.ok(documentService.listDocuments(clientId, year));","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01V1MD87rTGM5YNK2g5Wv3Lc\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:15.436Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_25a0c65300c7":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_25a0c65300c7","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# No range validation on year in the upload controller or service.\\n# Year could be 0, negative, or far future at upload time.\\n# The `year` filter in ExportRequest is for filtering existing documents ‚Äî not creating paths directly.\\n# The year IN the ZIP path comes from d.getYear() (the stored short value from the DB document).\\n# So: if year 0 or negative was stored at upload time, i‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# No range validation on year in the upload controller or service.\\n# Year could be 0, negative, or far fut‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:22.914Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_cedf1b785de8":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_cedf1b785de8","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01JfeprwVARPG389ixtR4VNs\"} | ExportRequest.year: no range validation, but used only as DB query parameter ‚Äî no security impact.","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01JfeprwVARPG389ixtR4VNs\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:22.947Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_95ab02d1c2a0":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_95ab02d1c2a0","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# One more check: the `loadOwnedClients` does validateOwnership (which uses the passed clientIds)\\n# then returns findAllById(clientIds) ‚Äî meaning the SECOND query also uses clientIds from the request,\\n# not from the validated list.\\n# This means: if adminId check passes for all found clients, but the ID list had non-existent IDs,\\n# those are silently dropped in the second findAllBy‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# One more check: the `loadOwnedClients` does validateOwnership (which uses the passed clientIds)\\n# then r‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:30.530Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_7bf0087effe4":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_7bf0087effe4","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01HXYZRq96WR94jeNvHacjA9\"} | Ownership isolation is correct end-to-end.\nSQL injection: JPA parameterized queries used ‚Äî not applicable.","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01HXYZRq96WR94jeNvHacjA9\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:30.559Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_828e466999e8":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_828e466999e8","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# Final check on frontend parseFilename regex for any risk\\n# Regex: /filename=\\\"?([^\\\"]+)\\\"?/\\n# Server sets Content-Disposition: attachment; filename=\\\"clients-export-2026-06-17.csv\\\"\\n# The filename comes from: \\\"clients-export-\\\" + LocalDate.now() + \\\".csv\\\"\\n# LocalDate.now().toString() returns ISO-8601 like \\\"2026-06-17\\\" ‚Äî no special chars\\n# This value is server-generated, not‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# Final check on frontend parseFilename regex for any risk\\n# Regex: /filename=\\\"?([^\\\"]+)\\\"?/\\n# Server se‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:39.759Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwsvvtj_48e82811b09b":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwsvvtj_48e82811b09b"