documentService.upload(clientId, year, file, uploadedBy);\n42:                                                  @RequestParam(\"year\") int year) {\n43:        return ResponseEntity.ok(documentService.listDocuments(clientId, year));","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01V1MD87rTGM5YNK2g5Wv3Lc\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:15.436Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwtkgr1_eb329e798e2b":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwtkgr1_eb329e798e2b","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"command\":\"# No range validation on year in the upload controller or service.\\n# Year could be 0, negative, or far future at upload time.\\n# The `year` filter in ExportRequest is for filtering existing documents ‚Äî not creating paths directly.\\n# The year IN the ZIP path comes from d.getYear() (the stored short value from the DB document).\\n# So: if year 0 or negative was stored at upload time, i‚Ä¶","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"command\":\"# No range validation on year in the upload controller or service.\\n# Year could be 0, negative, or far fut‚Ä¶","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:22.914Z","title":"Bash","type":"command_run"},"obs_mqwtkgr1_05a99f67f48e":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwtkgr1_05a99f67f48e","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01JfeprwVARPG389ixtR4VNs\"} | ExportRequest.year: no range validation, but used only as DB query parameter ‚Äî no security impact.","sessionId":"6c35a5fd-da10-4150-b228-cbb30c73ea0e","subtitle":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01JfeprwVARPG389ixtR4VNs\"}","timestamp":"2026-06-17T21:08:22.947Z","title":"post_tool_use","type":"other"},"obs_mqwtkgr1_18e5c4b5803d":{"concepts":[],"confidence":0.3,"facts":[],"files":[],"id":"obs_mqwtkgr1_18e5c4b5803d","importance":5,"narrative":"{\"toolUseId\":\"toolu_01HXYZRq96WR94jeNvHacjA9\"} | Ownership isolation is correct end-to-end.\nSQL injection: JP